INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (227,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',3,'You can use it to monitor, store, and access your log files from Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) instances, AWS CloudTrail, Route 53, and other sources. It enables you to centralize the logs from all of your systems, applications, and AWS services that you use, in a single, highly scalable service. You can then easily view them, search them for specific error codes or patterns, filter them based on specific fields, or archive them securely for future analysis. It also enables you to see all of your logs, regardless of their source, as a single and consistent flow of events ordered by time.',56);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (228,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',4,'It is a fully managed service that makes it easy for developers to create, publish, maintain, monitor, and secure APIs at any scale. APIs act as the front door for applications to access data, business logic, or functionality from your backend services. Using it, you can create RESTful APIs and WebSocket APIs that enable real-time two-way communication applications. It supports containerized and serverless workloads, as well as web applications.',56);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (229,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',2,'It is a service that enables governance, compliance, operational auditing, and risk auditing of your Amazon Web Services account. With this service, you can log, continuously monitor, and retain account activity related to actions across your Amazon Web Services infrastructure. It provides event history of your Amazon Web Services account activity, including actions taken through the Amazon Management Console, Amazon SDKs, command line tools, and other Amazon Web Services services. This event history simplifies security analysis, resource change tracking, and troubleshooting.',57);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (230,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',3,'It helps you manage, retrieve, and rotate database credentials, API keys, and other secrets throughout their lifecycles.',57);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (231,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',4,'It is a fully managed container orchestration service that simplifies your deployment, management, and scaling of containerized applications. Simply describe your application and the resources required, and it will launch, monitor, and scale your application across flexible compute options with automatic integrations to other supporting AWS services that your application needs. Perform system operations such as creating custom scaling and capacity rules, and observe and query data from application logs and telemetry.',57);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (232,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',2,'It is a command line interface (CLI) that you can use to quickly launch and manage containerized applications on AWS. It simplifies running applications on Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS), AWS Fargate, and AWS App Runner.',58);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (233,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',3,'It is a cloud-based integrated development environment (IDE) that lets you write, run, and debug your code with just a browser. It includes a code editor, debugger, and terminal. It comes prepackaged with essential tools for popular programming languages, including JavaScript, Python, PHP, and more, so you don’t need to install files or configure your development machine to start new projects.',58);
INSERT  INTO `answer`(`id`,`created_date`,`a_order`,`text`,`question_id`) VALUES (234,'2023-06-14 16:53:22',4,'It is a fully managed container orchestration service that simplifies your deployment, management, and scaling of containerized applications. Simply describe your application and the resources required, and it will launch, monitor, and scale your application across flexible compute options with automatic integrations to other supporting AWS services that your application needs. Perform system operations such as creating custom scaling and capacity rules, and observe and query data from application logs and telemetry.',58);
